# The `RegionNodeBase` Class Template Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a> represents a subregion or a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> that is part of a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a>.

### getParent() {#a79b09475f3753504a26dc312d572112e}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class Tr&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>RegionT &#42; llvm::RegionNodeBase&lt; Tr &gt;::getParent () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Get the parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a> of this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a>.

The parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a> is the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a> this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a> belongs to. If for example a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> is element of two Regions, there exist two RegionNodes for this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a>. Each with the <a href="#a79b09475f3753504a26dc312d572112e">getParent()</a> function pointing to the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a> this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a> belongs to.

## Private Member Attributes

### entry {#a9d90c68111dc3faef3cb59b676d767ff}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class Tr&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>PointerIntPair&lt;BlockT &#42;, 1, bool&gt; llvm::RegionNodeBase&lt; Tr &gt;::entry</>}>
This is the entry basic block that starts this region node.

If this is a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a>, then entry is just the basic block, that this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a> represents. Otherwise it is the entry of this (Sub)<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a>.

In the BBtoRegionNode map of the parent of this node, BB will always map to this node no matter which kind of node this one is.

The node can hold either a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/region">Region</a> or a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a>. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> one bit to save, if this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a> is a subregion or <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/regionnode">RegionNode</a>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/regioninfo-h/#l00133">133</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/regioninfo-h">RegionInfo.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
